s=3D"default-content-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"the-anova-table">The ANOVA table</h=
3><p>ANOVA results are typically displayed in an ANOVA table. An ANOVA tabl=
e includes:</p><ul>
          <li>Source: the sources of variation including the factor being e=
xamined (in our case, lot), error and total.</li>
          <li>DF: degrees of freedom for each source of variation.</li>
          <li>Sum of Squares: sum of squares (SS) for each source of variat=
ion along with the total from all sources.</li>
          <li>Mean Square: sum of squares divided by its associated degrees=
 of freedom.</li>
          <li>F Ratio: the mean square of the factor (lot) divided by the m=
ean square of the error.</li>
          <li>Prob &gt; F: the p-value.</li>
        </ul><p><em>Table 2: ANOVA table with results from our torque measu=
rements</em></p></div><div class=3D"table-wrapper"><div class=3D"table stri=
